byline.contributor: Suliman Ali Zway contributed reporting from Tripoli, Libya.

lead_paragraph: Abdullah al-Thinni had faced hostile questioning inside Parliament, and demands for his resignation from armed demonstrators outside.

headline.print_headline: Libyan Prime Minister Survives Attempt on His Life Amid Protests
headline.main: Libyan Prime Minister Survives Assassination Attempt Amid Protests

abstract: Libyan Prime Min Abdullah al-Thinni survives assassination attempt following hostile questioning inside Parliament and demands for his resignation from armed protesters outside.
